This paper deals with the containment problem for monadic datalog over unordered unranked labeled trees, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the expressive power of monadic datalog on various representations of unranked trees, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and formal languages (cs.FL). Finally, the paper presents a positive answer to a question posed by Abiteboul et al., which is a topic related to computational complexity (cs.CC).
